Dia. 03 Descending Move, Dead
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black wants to expand his living space and live with the descending move at 1.
\par \cf1\b White's placement at 2\cf0\b0  is the \cf1\b right attack\cf0\b0  again.
\par
\par If Black plays at 3, White blocks at 4 and captures Black easily.
\par If White plays at A instead of 4, Black is still dead.
\par
\par
